173
00:09:16.059 --> 00:09:18.059
Rest assured, I've got to cover it.

174
00:09:18.059 --> 00:09:19.059
Don't you worry.

175
00:09:19.059 --> 00:09:21.059
You'll have the cornea soon enough.

176
00:09:21.059 --> 00:09:24.570
Can we just use my kidneys?

177
00:09:24.570 --> 00:09:26.570
I mean, I'll give both to save him.

178
00:09:26.570 --> 00:09:31.570
Even if we could use yours, you'd still have the cost of surgery and recovery.

179
00:09:32.570 --> 00:09:35.570
Besides, we're not even sure if they're compatible.

180
00:09:35.570 --> 00:09:38.950
You really need to find that half a million.

181
00:09:38.950 --> 00:09:53.909
Sorry I failed you.

182
00:09:53.909 --> 00:09:58.019
It's all moveful.

183
00:09:58.019 --> 00:09:59.019
Give it a stay.

184
00:09:59.019 --> 00:10:00.210
She's in it.

185
00:10:00.210 --> 00:10:10.179
She'll be begging to donate her cornea.

186
00:10:10.179 --> 00:10:11.179
Janitor lives.

187
00:10:11.179 --> 00:10:17.230
Mr. Walker, my father's kidneys are failing.

188
00:10:17.230 --> 00:10:19.230
And he does not have much time left.

189
00:10:19.230 --> 00:10:21.230
Please, I'm begging you.

190
00:10:21.230 --> 00:10:25.149
Just hold that to you guys.

191
00:10:25.149 --> 00:10:26.279
Relax.

192
00:10:26.279 --> 00:10:29.139
I'm just here to make you an offer.

193
00:10:29.139 --> 00:10:32.139
My friend recently got in a car accident and lost his eye.

194
00:10:32.139 --> 00:10:34.529
He needs a cornea.

195
00:10:34.529 --> 00:10:38.529
If you were willing to donate yours, it would give you half a million dollars.

196
00:10:38.529 --> 00:10:39.529
What do you say?

197
00:10:39.529 --> 00:10:42.230
