Who gave you permission to enter my office?

272
00:15:29.299 --> 00:15:34.639
Mr. Walker, I was just here to clean your office.

273
00:15:34.639 --> 00:15:37.639
Do you think someone like you deserves to clean my office?

274
00:15:37.639 --> 00:15:40.639
You people are nothing but filth.

275
00:15:40.639 --> 00:15:42.639
You injured my son.

276
00:15:42.639 --> 00:15:44.639
You ruined the company banquet.

277
00:15:44.639 --> 00:15:46.639
And your father's filthy blood got all over him.

278
00:15:46.639 --> 00:15:49.639
You're lucky that he didn't get infected.

279
00:15:49.639 --> 00:15:51.639
Because I would have made you people pay.

280
00:15:51.639 --> 00:15:52.639
Now get out.

281
00:15:52.639 --> 00:15:53.639
Leave Walker Group.

282
00:15:53.639 --> 00:15:54.639
You're not welcome here.

283
00:15:54.639 --> 00:15:57.639
Wait, Mrs. Walker, I really need this job.

284
00:15:57.639 --> 00:16:01.639
My father's kidneys are failing, and I'm the only one earning money.

285
00:16:01.639 --> 00:16:03.639
I really need this job.

286
00:16:03.639 --> 00:16:05.639
Your father's kidney failure is not my problem.

287
00:16:05.639 --> 00:16:07.639
Please, Mrs. Walker, I'll do anything.

288
00:16:07.639 --> 00:16:10.639
Don't touch me. Get out now.

289
00:16:10.639 --> 00:16:16.980
You have no idea how filthy you are, do you?

290
00:16:16.980 --> 00:16:20.330
Mom, I'm going to assign Greta to do the cleaning.

291
00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:23.330
And you chose this one to clean my office.

292
00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:26.330
Look at her wrinkled clothes and her torn shoes.

293
00:16:26.330 --> 00:16:29.330
She's trash. How can she do a proper job?

294
00:16:29.330 --> 00:16:31.330
If we did that, we'd have to hire another janitor.

295
00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:35.330
Besides, Greta's already here, and she's doing her job.

296
00:16:35.330 --> 00:16:38.639
It just saves the company money.

297
00:16:38.639 --> 00:16:41.639
Until I get Greta's corn, yeah, I can't let Mom fire her.

298
00:16:41.639 --> 00:16:43.639
Her Jackson will be a big mouth.

299
00:16:43.639 --> 00:16:47.179
Fine. Do whatever you want.

300
00:16:47.179 --> 00:16:50.179
But when you clean my office, wear shoe covers.

301
00:16:50.179 --> 00:16:52.179
And don't even think about stealing anything.

302
00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:55.179
If I catch you, you'll regret it.

303
00:16:55.179 --> 00:16:56.179
Now get out.

304
00:16:56.179 --> 00:17:04.420
Any news about your sister?

305
00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:06.420
I've got all my resources checking the guest list.

306
00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:09.420
I've also installed cameras in every corner of the banquet hall.

307
00:17:09.420 --> 00:17:11.420
If Claire comes back, we'll know immediately.

308
00:17:11.420 --> 00:17:19.950
It's all my fault.

309
00:17:19.950 --> 00:17:21.660
Where are you?

310
00:17:21.660 --> 00:17:25.299
I didn't realize how close you were.

311
00:17:25.299 --> 00:17:29.839
Next time, if you come back, I'll never let you go again.

312
00:17:29.839 --> 00:17:40.059
Can we talk?

313
00:17:40.059 --> 00:17:47.940
My mother was awful to you the other day.

314
00:17:47.940 --> 00:17:49.940
I'm here to apologize on her behalf.

315
00:17:49.940 --> 00:17:52.839
This card has $10,000 on it.

316
00:17:52.839 --> 00:17:55.839
I've considered a compensation of the Walker family.

317
00:17:55.839 --> 00:17:57.829
I can't accept that.

318
00:17:57.829 --> 00:17:59.829
I know about your father's medical condition.

319
00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:01.900
But consider it alone.

320
00:18:01.900 --> 00:18:03.900
I can pay me back whenever you can.

321
00:18:03.900 --> 00:18:04.900
How does that sound?

322
00:18:04.900 --> 00:18:07.049
Okay.

323
00:18:07.049 --> 00:18:10.640
Thank you.

324
00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:11.640
Now let's see.

325
00:18:11.640 --> 00:18:21.329
Why are you eating just the crust?

326
00:18:21.329 --> 00:18:22.329
I like the crust.

327
00:18:22.329 --> 00:18:23.329
It's chewy.

328
00:18:23.329 --> 00:18:26.329
I'll take the soft part for my dad.

329
00:18:26.329 --> 00:18:28.619
So you have a soft part?

330
00:18:28.619 --> 00:18:29.710
Why aren't you eating it?

331
00:18:29.710 --> 00:18:30.710
I like the crust.

332
00:18:30.710 --> 00:18:31.710
It's chewy.

333
00:18:31.710 --> 00:18:32.710
All right.

334
00:18:32.710 --> 00:18:34.710
Miss Walker, I think it's getting kind of late.

335
00:18:34.710 --> 00:18:37.710
I should probably get back to take care of my dad.

336
00:18:37.710 --> 00:18:38.710
Of course.

337
00:18:38.710 --> 00:18:40.380
Do you need a red?

338
00:18:40.380 --> 00:18:41.380
No, that's okay.

339
00:18:41.380 --> 00:18:42.380
You've already done more than enough for me.

340
00:18:42.380 --> 00:18:44.380
And I promise I will pay you back.

341
00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:46.339
Okay.

342
00:18:46.339 --> 00:18:47.339
Can I take this?

343
00:18:47.339 --> 00:18:55.099
If my sister hadn't been abandoned.

344
00:18:55.099 --> 00:18:57.099
She'd be about this age now.

345
00:18:57.099 --> 00:18:59.539
Could it be?

346
00:18:59.539 --> 00:19:00.539
No.

347
00:19:00.539 --> 00:19:06.130
I'm done with this.

348
00:19:06.130 --> 00:19:07.130
You're going home.

349
00:19:07.130 --> 00:19:10.130
I don't want to be a burden on you anymore.

350
00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:12.579
Time to be okay.

351
00:19:12.579 --> 00:19:15.579
Walker's feeling really bad about what happened at the banquet.

352
00:19:15.579 --> 00:19:17.579
This is Walker even promoted me.

353
00:19:17.579 --> 00:19:19.579
After hearing about our situation.

354
00:19:19.579 --> 00:19:20.579
Really?

355
00:19:20.579 --> 00:19:22.579
You're not lying to me?

356
00:19:22.579 --> 00:19:24.579
No, of course not.

357
00:19:24.579 --> 00:19:25.700
It's the truth.

358
00:19:25.700 --> 00:19:30.950
Look, she even gave me a $10,000 advancement.

359
00:19:30.950 --> 00:19:32.210
Good.

360
00:19:32.210 --> 00:19:34.210
Maybe this is Walker.

361
00:19:34.210 --> 00:19:39.339
It's just strict on the outside, but she's a good person at heart.

362
00:19:39.339 --> 00:19:40.339
Yeah.

363
00:19:40.339 --> 00:19:43.940
She's not so bad.

364
00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:50.549
Really, it's time to take the fruit platter to miss Walker's office.

365
00:19:50.549 --> 00:19:52.549
I'm busy, I'm busy, I'm busy.

366
00:19:52.549 --> 00:19:58.240
Greta, take the fruit platter to Mrs. Walker's office.

367
00:19:58.240 --> 00:20:01.460
Do you remember where she likes apples?

368
00:20:01.460 --> 00:20:02.559
Oh.

369
00:20:02.559 --> 00:20:14.950
Okay.

370
00:20:14.950 --> 00:20:16.950
Mrs. Walker, here's your fruit platter.

371
00:20:16.950 --> 00:20:19.559
Who told you to come in here?

372
00:20:19.559 --> 00:20:21.559
I lose my appetite just knowing you've touched it.

373
00:20:21.559 --> 00:20:28.059
Let's be tight for more.

374
00:20:28.059 --> 00:20:30.059
I cut these apples for you.

375
00:20:30.059 --> 00:20:39.640
Like this.

376
00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:43.849
Who taught you to do this?

377
00:20:43.849 --> 00:20:44.849
Mom, what's going on?

378
00:20:44.849 --> 00:20:48.069
Mom, did this little tramp mess up again?

379
00:20:48.069 --> 00:20:50.069
I'll take care of her for you.

380
00:20:50.069 --> 00:20:51.970
No, no, it's fine.

381
00:20:51.970 --> 00:20:52.970
You can go now.

382
00:20:52.970 --> 00:21:00.349
Haven't you noticed how much Greta resembles Clara?

383
00:21:00.349 --> 00:21:02.349
She's just saying that because it was Clara so much.

384
00:21:02.349 --> 00:21:04.349
She's just that dirty, janitor's daughter.

385
00:21:04.349 --> 00:21:06.349
There's no way she could be Clara.

386
00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:08.349
Yeah, but what if she's not really David's daughter?

387
00:21:08.349 --> 00:21:09.349
What are you talking about?

388
00:21:09.349 --> 00:21:10.349
They're exactly alike.

389
00:21:10.349 --> 00:21:13.349
If she really was Clara, don't you think I'd recognize her?

390
00:21:13.349 --> 00:21:15.349
Or Mom would recognize her for that matter?

391
00:21:15.349 --> 00:21:19.609
From now on, Greta will bring me my fruit platter every day.

392
00:21:19.609 --> 00:21:21.609
And give her a $3,000 race.

393
00:21:21.609 --> 00:21:23.609
Mom, that's a bit short.

394
00:21:23.609 --> 00:21:26.609
Charlotte, I need your help looking into Greta's background.

395
00:21:26.609 --> 00:21:28.670
Don't miss a single clue.

396
00:21:28.670 --> 00:21:39.990
Your father's condition has worsened.

397
00:21:39.990 --> 00:21:43.119
We'll need to settle that surgery bill within three days.

398
00:21:43.119 --> 00:21:45.119
Dr. Orr, can't we just use my...

399
00:21:45.119 --> 00:21:47.119
We've already tested your kidneys.

400
00:21:47.119 --> 00:21:49.119
They're not compatible with your father's.

401
00:21:49.119 --> 00:21:54.119
As far as the payment goes, half a million dollars was the lowest I could negotiate.

402
00:21:54.119 --> 00:22:00.119
Listen, I understand it's almost impossible for a regular family to rake in that much money.

403
00:22:00.119 --> 00:22:02.119
Maybe it's better to let it go.

404
00:22:02.119 --> 00:22:13.859
I'm making it half a million dollars.

405
00:22:13.859 --> 00:22:15.859
Everything I have is worthless.

406
00:22:15.859 --> 00:22:19.740
Except the ring, I still have the ring on me.

407
00:22:19.740 --> 00:22:22.190
It must be worth something.

408
00:22:22.190 --> 00:22:30.220
I can use it to pay for my father's treatment.

409
00:22:30.220 --> 00:22:32.220
I must have dropped it at the banquet.

410
00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:35.690
After her find it.

411
00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:58.160
Where are you?

412
00:22:58.160 --> 00:22:59.349
Mrs. Walker.

413
00:22:59.349 --> 00:23:01.349
Someone's at the banquet hall right now.

414
00:23:01.349 --> 00:23:03.890
Really?

415
00:23:03.890 --> 00:23:05.890
Someone's actually at the banquet hall?

416
00:23:05.890 --> 00:23:06.890
Who is it?

417
00:23:06.890 --> 00:23:07.890
I've already connected the surveillance feed.

418
00:23:07.890 --> 00:23:13.430
Take a look.

419
00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:14.430
It's her?

420
00:23:14.430 --> 00:23:20.119
Mrs. Walker, please, I did not steal that ring.

421
00:23:20.119 --> 00:23:24.119
I really need to get my dad to the hospital. He's all I have left.

422
00:23:24.119 --> 00:23:25.119
It's her.

423
00:23:25.119 --> 00:23:31.829
I should have realized sooner.

424
00:23:31.829 --> 00:23:32.829
Quick.

425
00:23:32.829 --> 00:23:33.829
Get the car.

426
00:23:33.829 --> 00:23:35.930
We're going to the banquet hall.

427
00:23:35.930 --> 00:23:36.930
I need to meet my daughter.

428
00:23:36.930 --> 00:23:45.839
Did you lose something?

429
00:23:45.839 --> 00:23:51.819
Uh, yeah, Mrs. Walker, I just lost something.

430
00:23:51.819 --> 00:23:53.819
I'm so sorry to disturb you.

431
00:23:53.819 --> 00:24:00.049
What exactly did you lose?

432
00:24:00.049 --> 00:24:01.049
Lost my...

433
00:24:01.049 --> 00:24:02.240
Greta!

434
00:24:02.240 --> 00:24:04.940
I said you took my hairpin.

435
00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:06.940
I was wondering where I went.

436
00:24:06.940 --> 00:24:12.589
I finally caught you.

437
00:24:12.589 --> 00:24:15.589
Now, what do you have to say for yourself?

438
00:24:15.589 --> 00:24:19.589
I just found it in the banquet hall. I didn't steal it.

439
00:24:19.589 --> 00:24:23.589
This diamond hairpin is very valuable.

440
00:24:23.589 --> 00:24:26.589
You must have lost it during the company's banquet.

441
00:24:26.589 --> 00:24:30.589
And you must have picked it up and decided to keep it.

442
00:24:30.589 --> 00:24:33.589
If it hadn't come back for it, you would have stolen it.

443
00:24:33.589 --> 00:24:34.589
You're so into me arm.

444
00:24:34.589 --> 00:24:36.589
So it was just false hope.

445
00:24:36.589 --> 00:24:39.009
She was here to steal.

446
00:24:39.009 --> 00:24:41.900
Get after my sight.

447
00:24:41.900 --> 00:24:44.900
You're not allowed to enter the company without permission anymore.

448
00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:46.900
Or I'll have your legs broken.

449
00:24:46.900 --> 00:24:49.900
No, no, I was really looking for something. I'm not lying.

450
00:24:49.900 --> 00:24:53.250
No, I really was looking for something.

451
00:24:53.250 --> 00:24:54.250
I'm not...

452
00:24:54.250 --> 00:24:55.250
Stay where you are.

453
00:24:55.250 --> 00:24:56.250
Don't come near me, trash.

454
00:24:56.250 --> 00:24:59.250
All right, but Mrs. Walker, please just hear me out.

455
00:24:59.250 --> 00:25:01.250
I don't want to hear it.

456
00:25:01.250 --> 00:25:02.250
Security!

457
00:25:02.250 --> 00:25:04.250
It's low life out of here.

458
00:25:04.250 --> 00:25:15.759
Dr. Aurora, how's my dad doing?

459
00:25:15.759 --> 00:25:18.759
His condition is critical. We need to operate immediately.

460
00:25:18.759 --> 00:25:20.759
Greta, you have two options.

461
00:25:20.759 --> 00:25:23.759
Find the money for the surgery in the next two days.

462
00:25:23.759 --> 00:25:26.759
Or let them go in peace.

463
00:25:26.759 --> 00:25:28.859
What's your decision?

464
00:25:29.859 --> 00:25:32.859
I can't do that, Dr. Aurora, please.

465
00:25:32.859 --> 00:25:34.859
Save him. I'll do anything.

466
00:25:34.859 --> 00:25:36.859
I've done everything I can.

467
00:25:36.859 --> 00:25:39.859
Maybe ask your friends or family if they can lend you the money?

468
00:25:39.859 --> 00:25:49.539
Who would be willing to give me that much money?

469
00:25:49.539 --> 00:26:06.329
I'm just here to make you an offer.

470
00:26:06.329 --> 00:26:09.549
My friend recently got in a car accident and lost his eye.

471
00:26:09.549 --> 00:26:11.940
He needs a cornea.

472
00:26:11.940 --> 00:26:17.130
If you were willing to donate yours, it would give you half a million dollars.

473
00:26:17.130 --> 00:26:18.130
What do you say?

474
00:26:18.130 --> 00:26:26.880
Who's calling me at this hour?

475
00:26:26.880 --> 00:26:30.220
Mr. Walker? It's me.

